NATION BRIEFS																																												 New Delhi, Nov.19: The age limit in the pension scheme for below-poverty line families will be cut to 60 years from 65.																																												Prime Minister Manmohan Singh made the announcement today while launching the Indira Gandhi National Old Age Pension Scheme, saying its scope would be broadened to include poor widows and the handicapped. 																																												New Delhi (PTI): The Indian Air Force is planning to induct stealth technology and super manoeuvrability in its proposed fifth generation fighters to be jointly developed with Russia, defence minister A.K. Antony told the Lok Sabha.																																												Ghaziabad (PTI): The families of two victims of the Nithari killings have filed a complaint against another victims father for withdrawing his statement against 																																												accused Moninder Singh Pandher. They claimed the statement was withdrawn to give benefit to the accused. 																																												New Delhi (PTI): Defence minister A.K. Antony said an apex committee had been set up to monitor work on Admiral Gorshkov as the delivery schedule of the aircraft carrier was quot;running slow quot;. He told the Lok Sabha that Russia had submitted a revised master schedule indicating a delay in the project.																																												Aligarh (PTI): Three persons were crushed to death and six seriously injured by a goods train at a railway crossing on Monday. The mishap occurred when some persons tried to cross over despite the road barriers being closed.																																												 Madurai (PTI): A case has been registered against a police inspector for allegedly threatening a person at gun point and taking Rs 19,000 from him. Ramachandran apparently stopped the vehicle in which he was taking Ganesan to the police station in connection with a theft and forced him to hand over the money, which he said was stolen from a local shop.
